        "name": "Club",
        "text": "*Melee Weapon Attack:* ATK[STR] to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. *Hit:* DMG[1d4 + STR] bludgeoning damage."
      },
      {
        "name": "Luring Song",
        "text": "[name] sings a magical melody. Every humanoid and giant within 300 ft. of [name] that can hear the song must succeed on a DC 11 Wisdom saving throw or be charmed until the song ends. [name] must take a bonus action on its subsequent turns to continue singing. It can stop singing at any time. The song ends if [name] is incapacitated.\n  While charmed by [name], a target is incapacitated and ignores the songs of other harpies. If the charmed target is more than 5 ft. away from [name], the must move on its turn toward [name] by the most direct route. It doesn't avoid opportunity attacks, but before moving into damaging terrain, such as lava or a pit, and whenever it takes damage from a source other than [name], a target can repeat the saving throw. A creature can also repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its turns. If a creature's saving throw is successful, the effect ends on it.\n  A target that successfully saves is immune to this harpy's song for the next 24 hours."
      }
    ]
